# CodeSage — what it is

Self-hosted, codebase-aware QA platform: connect Git repos → index (AST graph + vector chunks in
PostgreSQL) → LLM distills workflows/pages/permissions/data-flows → grounded chat answers for
developers and end-users. Uncertainty becomes an expert question, not a hallucination.

Full docs in `docs/` (start at `docs/README.md`). Decisions in `docs/adr/`.

# The boundary you must respect

```
React (apps/web) → Node non-blocking APIs (apps/api) → Python heavy work (services/* + packages/py-core)
                                  └──────────── PostgreSQL: single datastore ───────────┘
```

- **Node never blocks on heavy work.** It does auth/CRUD/static/WS/webhooks and **enqueues jobs**
  or **proxies to the Python RAG service**.
- **Python owns all heavy/blocking work** (sync, parse, embed, graph, distill, retrieve, QA).
- **Business logic lives in `packages/py-core`**; `services/rag` and `services/worker` are thin.
- **Single datastore = PostgreSQL** (+pgvector). No Redis/Qdrant/Neo4j/broker in MVP — write an
  ADR before adding any data system.
- **Open source only**; private code/tokens never leave the network.

# Before any non-trivial change

Read the nearest `AGENTS.md` and follow the Definition of Done in `docs/development-workflow.md`.
